To test this possibility, we built a second set of CSP clusters, this time following the present-day age distribution (i.e. pseudo-age distributions in G11a,b and G14). For this we assumed a simple Gaussian distribution centred at 570 Myr and with FWHM ranging from 300 to 100 Myr (cf. Fig. \ref{sfh2}). The resulting SEDs are shown in Figs. \ref{SEDs2} and \ref{CaIIK2}, where they are compared directly with the observed W3 spectrum.

